Here you will find the following SlackBuilds:

distcc-masq-client:

This is a 'masquerade' mode distcc client for both gcc/g++ and clang/clang++.

distcc-masq-server:

This is a 'masquerade' mode distcc server.  On x86_64, it is a full multiarch
cross-compiling server -- it can build for i486 and x86_64, and for arm if the
arm-x-toolchain package is installed.

arm-x-toolchain:

This is Stuart Winter's x-toolchain (from the Slackware ARM devtools) packaged
to work with distcc-client and distcc-server.

References:

For a full description of distcc 'masquerade' mode, see
  http://distcc.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/doc/web/man/distcc_1.html#TOC_13
See also
  ftp://ftp.arm.slackware.com/slackwarearm/slackwarearm-devtools/x-toolchain/
